This paper proposes a new format for representing constraint networks, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as constraint satisfaction problems are a common topic in AI. The paper also discusses the representation of constraints in extension or intension, which relates to data structures (cs.DS) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The use of XML as a format for representing the constraint networks is relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE).
